</llm_integration>

## Testing & Debugging

<testing_rules>
- Validate bot changes with backups and log monitoring on production, or on a separate staging stack if available
- Use `.bot count` to check active bots
- Use `.bot stats` for performance metrics
- Enable debug logging: `.debug on`
- Check logs: `tail -f env/dist/logs/Server.log | grep -i bot` (adjust path if logs use `/data/logs/`)
- Test bot behavior in different scenarios (combat, movement, healing)
- Verify no conflicts with other modules
- Monitor bot performance during testing
</testing_rules>

## Common Issues

<common_issues>
- **Bots not spawning**: Verify AiPlayerbot.Enabled=1, check RandomBotAutologin, verify bot count setting
- **Bots stuck in combat**: Use `.bot unstuck`, increase update frequency, check pathfinding
- **Bots not grouping**: Verify AltsEnabled=1, check party size limits, verify bot availability
- **Bots causing lag**: Reduce bot count, increase update interval, disable unnecessary features
- **Bot not healing**: Verify healing spells known, check mana, verify healing strategy active
- **Bot not casting**: Verify spell known, check mana/resource, verify cooldowns, check target validity
</common_issues>

## Integration with Other Modules

<module_integration>
- **Mythic Plus**: Bots support Mythic+ dungeons, difficulty scaling applies
- **Solocraft**: Bots count toward party size, scaling adjusts for bot presence
- **Progression System**: Bots respect level brackets, follow progression rules
- **Challenge Modes**: Bots can participate in hardcore/iron man modes
- Test bot integration with each module
- Verify no conflicts or unintended interactions
</module_integration>

## Database Tables

<database_tables>
- **ai_playerbot_config**: Bot configuration and state (name, class, level, equipment, talents)
- **ai_playerbot_strategy**: Bot strategy definitions (action priorities, spell selections)
- **ai_playerbot_tactics**: Bot tactic definitions (movement, combat, healing priorities)
- Backup playerbots database before major changes
- Verify table structure after schema updates
</database_tables>

## Best Practices

<best_practices>
- Start with low bot count and increase gradually
- Monitor performance continuously
- Use appropriate strategies for bot class/role
- Test bot behavior in different scenarios
- Keep bot configuration documented
- Backup bot database regularly
- Update bot AI with new patches
- Optimize pathfinding for your maps
- Balance bot difficulty with player experience
- Use LLM integration for advanced behavior (optional)
</best_practices>

## Raid & Dungeon Support

<raid_support>
### Supported Raid Instances
- **Icecrown Citadel (ICC)**: Rotface, Saurfang, and other boss mechanics
- **Trial of the Champion (ToC)**: Ground combat mechanics with Black Knight, Desecration, Paletress
- **Hyjal Summit**: Elemental boss mechanics
- **Ulduar**: Complex boss mechanics
- **Naxxramas**: Classic raid mechanics

### Bot Raid Capabilities
- Multiple strategies per boss for different roles (tank/dps/heal)
- Threat management and positioning
- Spell rotation optimization for raid encounters
- Healing priority and mana management
- Crowd control and debuff handling
- Loot distribution among party members

### Raid Testing Best Practices
- Test bot behavior in a controlled way (staging or low-impact production window with rollback)
- Verify bot positioning and movement
- Check threat management and aggro handling
- Monitor bot spell rotation and cooldown usage
- Test healing coverage and mana management
- Verify no conflicts with other raid mechanics
</raid_support>

## Bot Movement & Navigation

<movement_mechanics>
### Pathfinding System
- Terrain-aware pathfinding with collision detection
- Distance-based update frequency optimization
- Waypoint following for quest and patrol routes
- Combat movement with threat-based positioning

### Flying Mount Mechanics
- **Active Descent**: Prevents hovering in TBC/WotLK zones
- **Terrain Clearance**: Avoids collision with terrain
- **Zone Restrictions**: Flying only in map 530 (Outland) and 571 (Northrend)
- **Classic Zones**: Ground pathfinding even with flying mounts
- **Mount Selection**: Automatic selection based on zone and speed requirements

### Movement Optimization
- Cache frequently used paths
- Limit pathfinding distance for distant targets
- Batch pathfinding updates
- Monitor pathfinding cache hit rate
- Reduce update frequency for distant bots
</movement_mechanics>

## LLM Integration Details

<llm_features>
### mod-playerbots-llm Configuration
- **Providers**: OpenAI (gpt-4 default), Claude, Ollama, custom providers
- **Vector Database**: Qdrant at http://localhost:6333
- **Embedding Model**: text-embedding-ada-002 (1536 dimensions)
- **Game Data Indexing**: 31k+ items, 3k+ quests, 100k+ creatures, 30k+ spells
- **Chat Features**: Whisper, party/raid, guild, say/yell with personalities
- **Conversation Memory**: 20 messages max history with 300s timeout
- **Response Delay**: 500-3000ms to simulate natural typing
- **Temperature**: 0.8 for creative responses, max 150 tokens per response

### LLM Performance Tuning
- **Worker Threads**: 4 LLM workers, 8 HTTP workers
- **Concurrent Requests**: Max 5 concurrent LLM requests
- **Async Operations**: All vector DB operations are async
- **Deferred Loading**: Knowledge loading deferred to prevent startup blocking
- **WoW Lore Context**: Enabled for era-appropriate responses

### Learning System
- **HeuristicLearner**: Pattern learning from interactions
- **Pattern Sync**: Every 5 seconds
- **Personality Adaptation**: Dynamic strategy adjustment
- **Memory Persistence**: Semantic memory in vector database
</llm_features>

## Architectural Considerations

<architecture>
### Group Operations Safety
- Arena group formation requires careful null checking
- Guild operations need defensive member validation
- Bot session validation essential for group operations
- Safe patterns: Group::RemoveMember uses GUID-based lookup, PlayerbotAI shutdown properly removes from groups

### Performance Tuning
- Bot count: 100-200 recommended per 4-core server
- Update interval: Default 100ms, adjustable for responsiveness
- SmartAI UPDATE_IC/OOC events impact CPU usage
- Spell proc checks on every damage event—keep efficient
- Pathfinding cache hit rate important for movement performance

### Spell & Ability System
- Class-specific spell rotations per specialization
- Cooldown management and resource tracking
- Threat-based ability selection
- Proc flag verification for triggered spells
- Spell family mask matching for class filtering
</architecture>
